</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="500">2.2. Generating a return slip in the return order</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you want to provide your customers with access to a return slip for a specific order, e.g. in the My Account area of the online store, generate a return slip in the corresponding return order.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Generating a return slip in the return order:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Orders » Edit orders</strong>.<br>
→ The order overview opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the return order for which a return slip should be created by clicking on the <strong>Order ID</strong>.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Receipts</strong> tab.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Create receipt</strong> drop-down menu, select the document <strong>Return slip</strong>.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings according to <a href="#table-orders-receipts-return-slip">Table 1</a>.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings to generate the return slip.<br>
→ A <strong>PDF file</strong> containing the generated return slip opens.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="600">3. Generating multiple return slips</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you wish to generate return slips for multiple orders at a time, use the search filter in the <strong>Orders » Fulfilment</strong> menu to determine the orders for which return slips should be generated. In addition, a status change can take place for the order after the return slips have been generated.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Generating multiple return slips:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Orders » Fulfilment » Generate return slips</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings according to <a href="#table-settings-fulfilment-return-slip">Table 2</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>gear-wheel icon</strong> to generate the return slips.<br>
→ A <strong>PDF file</strong> containing the return slips for the previously selected orders opens.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
